of ITW common stock as of December&nbsp;31, 2020. Because the granting of phantom stock units was discontinued in May 2012, Messrs.&nbsp;Henderson and Lenny, who joined the Board after that date, were not awarded phantom stock units upon joining the
Board. Phantom stock units are not transferable and have no voting rights. The units are payable in cash and are not included in the &#147;percent of class&#148; calculation. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

ITW. Briar Hall has sole voting and investment power with respect to 24,800,539 shares and shared voting and investment power with respect to 1,050,000 shares. The information above regarding the number of shares beneficially owned was provided in a
Schedule 13G/A filed with the SEC on January&nbsp;25, 2021. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

written request to Illinois Tool Works Inc., 155 Harlem Avenue, Glenview, IL, 60025, Attention: Secretary. You may also review the Company&#146;s SEC filings by visiting the Company&#146;s website at <U>https://investor.itw.com</U>. </P>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom53919_14"></A><A NAME="tx53919_51"></A>Executive Overview</B></FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Our Business Model </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="61%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="37%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">ITW is a global industrial manufacturing company comprised of seven industry leading segments. In late 2012, we launched our Enterprise Strategy with
the explicit goal of positioning ITW to deliver solid growth with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">best-in-class</FONT></FONT> margins and returns by focusing the entire Company on utilizing our highly differentiated
and proprietary ITW Business Model to its full potential.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The ITW Business Model is the core
source of our competitive advantage as a company. It drives our ability to win with customers and deliver differentiated returns for our shareholders. It is a powerful and proprietary set of strategic, operational, and cultural practices that have
been in a state of continual development and evolution inside the Company for over 30 years.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g53919g51a99.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">25 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Our Long-Term Enterprise Strategy </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In launching our long-term Enterprise Strategy, we undertook a complete review of our performance and began executing a multi-step approach to shift our primary growth
engine to organic revenue growth. Key initiatives of our Enterprise Strategy included portfolio realignment, business structure simplification, strategic sourcing, and diligent <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-application</FONT> of ITW&#146;s
80/20 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Front-to-Back</FONT></FONT> Process to optimize our segments for growth. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Since implementing
our Enterprise Strategy in 2012, and notwithstanding the impacts of the global pandemic in 2020, ITW&#146;s operating margin has increased from 15.9&nbsp;percent to 22.9&nbsp;percent and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> Return on
Average Invested Capital <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(After-tax</FONT> ROIC) has increased from 14.5&nbsp;percent to 26.2&nbsp;percent. Over this same period, we have grown Earnings Per Share (EPS) by a compound annual growth rate of
9&nbsp;percent, and the Company&#146;s market capitalization has nearly tripled. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>

</P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> measures. See <B>Appendix B</B> for information regarding these and other <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> measures, including reconciliations to the most directly comparable GAAP
measures. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">***</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">As of January&nbsp;1, 2012 and December&nbsp;31, 2020. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>2020: ITW Delivers Strong Operational and Financial Performance in a Challenging Environment </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2020, we leveraged the strength and resilience of the ITW Business Model to navigate the unprecedented challenges of the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">COVID-19</FONT> pandemic to deliver strong operational and financial performance while remaining committed to executing our strategy to deliver differentiated performance over the long-term. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our priorities in response to the pandemic were to: (1)&nbsp;protect the health and support the well-being of our ITW colleagues; (2)&nbsp;continue to serve the
Company&#146;s customers with excellence; (3)&nbsp;maintain financial strength, liquidity and strategic optionality; and (4)&nbsp;leverage the Company&#146;s strengths to position it to fully participate in the recovery. With our employees&#146;
health and well-being a top priority, we chose to use our strong financial foundation to reinforce our commitment to our people by continuing to employ all ITW colleagues through the entirety of the second quarter when the economic
</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">26 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
effects of the pandemic were at their most widespread and severe. Moreover, we decided not to initiate any enterprise-wide employment reduction mandates or programs at any point in 2020. These
decisions proved to be the right ones for the Company, our people, and our customers, and position us to win the recovery going into 2021. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Despite revenues being
down eleven percent year-over-year, we delivered EPS of $6.63, operating income of $2.9&nbsp;billion and highly resilient operating margin of 22.9&nbsp;percent (only down 120 basis points year-over-year despite the decision not to initiate any
enterprise-wide employment reduction mandates or programs to protect our employees), <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC of 26.2&nbsp;percent, and $2.6&nbsp;billion in free cash flow (see <B>Appendix B</B>). In addition, we raised
our dividend by seven percent and returned $2.1&nbsp;billion to shareholders in the form of dividends and share repurchases. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Throughout the pandemic, we maintained
our financial strength, liquidity, and strategic optionality. ITW&#146;s balance sheet remains strong with ample liquidity. The Company continued to generate strong cash flow throughout the year and, as a result, we did not need to issue any debt or
commercial paper in 2020, ending the year with approximately $2.6&nbsp;billion of cash and equivalents on hand. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Looking forward, we are aggressively executing our
&#147;Win the Recovery&#148; initiative while remaining focused on delivering differentiated performance over the long term through the continued execution of our Enterprise Strategy. Our aim is to position the Company to deliver <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">top-tier</FONT> performance over any five-year period, regardless of the environment, and firmly establish ITW as one of the world&#146;s best-performing, highest quality, and most respected industrial companies. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>How We Align Executive Compensation with the Enterprise Strategy </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Board of Directors and Compensation Committee are responsible for aligning executive incentives with the Company&#146;s strategy and the best interests of our
stockholders. The Board believes that the Company has a strong track record of thoughtful and diligent governance and execution with respect to aligning executive incentives, as evidenced by our stockholders&#146; overwhelmingly favorable support
for our annual advisory vote on executive compensation (exceeding 95&nbsp;percent over the past three years). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee uses our long-term
Enterprise Strategy as a framework to guide our executive compensation decisions. Our programs are designed to be highly performance-oriented, with rigorous financial goals to reward our executives for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">best-in-class</FONT></FONT> performance. We regularly review our annual and long-term incentive plan metrics to ensure ongoing alignment with the strategy&#146;s initiatives and performance objectives. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We link 50&nbsp;percent of our executives&#146; long-term incentive opportunity to performance awards consisting of share-based units and cash, with three rigorous
performance goals: three-year average (i)&nbsp;Operating Margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(ii)&nbsp;After-tax</FONT> ROIC, and (iii)&nbsp;EPS growth. The remaining 50&nbsp;percent of our long-term incentive opportunity consists of stock
option awards that only provide compensation value as our stock price increases. Notably, we do not provide any time-vested full value equity awards (i.e. restricted stock units) to our NEOs. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">27 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">

<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Variable pay makes up a substantial portion of CEO and NEO compensation, as illustrated in the graphs below. We believe that the mix of incentives in our executive
compensation plans continues to support the achievement of the current phase of our strategy and, as such, our 2020 incentive designs remained unchanged from 2019. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Comparison </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each component of the Company&#146;s compensation structure plays an integral role in motivating our executives to maximize ITW&#146;s
long-term performance potential. More than 77&nbsp;percent of the CEO&#146;s compensation is tied to the successful achievement of the Enterprise Strategy&#146;s long-term performance objectives. The following table shows total CEO pay relative to
the Company&#146;s cumulative TSR performance over the last 5 years. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</A>Executive Compensation Highlights </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="rom_153919_65"></A>Compensation Philosophy </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="92%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="33%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="65%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt" BGCOLOR="#00416a">
<TD HEIGHT="5" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Philosophy</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Key Components</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" ROWSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our executive compensation philosophy is designed to deliver competitive total compensation upon the achievement of our strategy objectives, which will attract, motivate
and retain leaders who drive the creation of long-term stockholder value.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Target total compensation is based on the median of our peer group and relevant external market data. Actual compensation is determined by
achievement of results based on our goals aligned with ITW&#146;s strategy.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Individual executive compensation is
then established based on an executive&#146;s scope of responsibility, impact on profitable growth, individual performance and breadth of experience.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> through short- and long-term incentives links
compensation to Company and business segment performance. This <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;pay-at-risk&#148;</FONT></FONT> aligns executive and stockholder interests to help ensure the short- and long-term
growth of ITW.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Objectives </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We emphasize a total compensation approach in establishing individual executive compensation levels with each component of compensation serving a specific purpose. In
addition to paying a competitive base salary, we use a mix of different performance-based components of compensation that reward different aspects of both Company and individual performance. Our 2020 executive compensation program consisted of both
fixed (base salary) and variable (annual cash incentives and long-term incentive compensation) components, as illustrated below: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>2020
Compensation Components </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Ongoing Best Practices </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We regularly review and refine our executive compensation program to ensure that it continues to address practices and policies that are aligned with our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy and the interests of our stockholders. In this regard, our 2020 compensation program reflects the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="46%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Do</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #ffffff; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Don&#146;t Do</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Pay for Performance</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>Our NEOs&#146; average total target compensation is 82% performance based.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Employment Agreements
</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not provide executive officers with employment agreements.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Robust Stock Ownership Guidelines</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have stock ownership guidelines for our executive officers of 6 x salary for CEO, 3 x salary for Vice Chairman, Executive Vice Presidents and CFO
and 2 x salary for Senior Vice Presidents.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Tax <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Gross-ups</FONT> </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not provide tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> as part of our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> agreements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual &#147;Say on Pay&#148; Vote</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We hold an annual advisory vote for our stockholders to review and approve our executive compensation programs.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Repricing </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not allow share repricing within our stock option plan.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Independent Compensation Consultant</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee: (1)&nbsp;engages an independent compensation consultant who advises the Committee on regulatory and other current
trends and key developments in executive compensation and (2)&nbsp;reassesses its consultant&#146;s independence annually.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Hedging/Pledging of Company
Equity Securities</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We prohibit executive officers and directors from engaging in any transaction that is designed to hedge or offset a
decrease in the market value of ITW common stock and from pledging ITW equity securities.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual CEO and NEO Performance Review</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee conducts an annual review of the performance of the CEO, as well as the other executive officers.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Dividends on Unvested Equity
Awards </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dividends accrued on unvested equity awards, including restricted stock units and performance share units, are not paid unless
awards vest.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual Review of Compensation Programs</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee, with input from its independent compensation consultant, conducts an annual review of our executive compensation
programs, considering business strategies, best practices and good governance.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Single-Trigger <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-In-Control</FONT></FONT> Vesting/Benefits</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not allow immediate
vesting of equity awards that are continued or replaced upon a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control;</FONT></FONT> all such awards allow only double-trigger vesting <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(change-in-</FONT></FONT><BR>control and termination).</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Clawback Policy</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>Our Compensation Recovery Policy provides for the reimbursement of incentives if a material financial restatement is required, whether
or not based on misconduct.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual Compensation Risk Assessment </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each year we perform an assessment of risks that could result from our executive compensation plans and programs.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">31 </P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Say on Pay Advisory Voting Results </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2018, 2019 and 2020, 95.5&nbsp;percent, 95.9&nbsp;percent and 95.0&nbsp;percent, respectively, of stockholder votes were cast to approve the compensation of our NEOs.
The Committee believes that this favorable vote is confirmation that our stockholders believe the pay of our NEOs is appropriately aligned with the performance of the Company and the interests of our stockholders. The Committee therefore determined
that it was not necessary to make any changes to our executive compensation practices during 2020 as a result of the Say on Pay votes. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom53919_16">
</A><A NAME="tx53919_53"></A>How We Make Compensation Decisions </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="rom_153919_66"></A>Role of the Compensation Committee </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee conducts an annual review of ITW&#146;s practices and the compensation of our executive officers to ensure: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The components of the total compensation package are aligned with the market to attract and retain the caliber of talent
required to deliver on our business strategies; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Compensation decisions are meaningfully differentiated to appropriately reflect the contributions of our highest
performers; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our incentive programs drive performance aligned with our strategy and the Company&#146;s culture and values.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In making its executive compensation decisions and recommendations, the Committee is guided by the following factors: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our compensation philosophy; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Compensation comparisons from a peer group of diversified multinational industrial companies with similar size, value, and
complexity; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our executive&#146;s contribution to our short- and long-term goals based on profitable growth and strong returns on
capital. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See &#147;Board of Directors and its Committees&#151;Compensation Committee&#148; under &#147;Proposal&nbsp;1&#151;Election&nbsp;of
Directors&#148; for more information about the function of the Committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Role of the Compensation Consultant </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee engages an independent advisor, Frederic W. Cook&nbsp;&amp; Co., Inc. (Cook), to work directly on its behalf and in cooperation with management to review
ITW&#146;s executive compensation program, confirm appropriateness of our peer companies, and assess our compensation governance process. In 2020, Cook conducted a marketplace review of the compensation we pay to our executive officers. Cook
provided the Committee with relevant market data, including a review of our pay and performance and that of our peers, reviewed the peer companies we use for comparison purposes, and benchmarked our compensation against our peer companies. Cook also
assisted the Committee with its assessment of compensation-related risk. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">With respect to CEO compensation, on an annual basis, Cook provides an independent
recommendation to the Committee for its consideration. In developing its recommendation, Cook relies on its understanding of ITW&#146;s business, strategy and compensation programs, as well as its own independent research and analysis including
ITW&#146;s peer group. Cook does not meet with the CEO with respect to his compensation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">32 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Peer Companies </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="48%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has identified a group of comparable companies, which we refer to as the peer group, to benchmark executive compensation and provide
competitive market data to be used in establishing and recommending each component of compensation. The peer group is reviewed annually by the Committee with assistance from Cook.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2020, the Committee utilized market data for pay benchmarking from a custom survey consisting
of the peers below, as provided by Aon. In addition, the Committee referred to market data from broad compensation surveys for manufacturing companies within Aon&#146;s TCM Online Executive survey, and the Willis Towers Watson Executive Compensation
survey using regression analysis.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Peer&nbsp;Group&nbsp;Selection&nbsp;Criteria:</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;U.S. publicly traded companies from ITW&#146;s same and related industries, identified based on
Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) codes;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-fourth</FONT> to four times our revenue and
market capitalization with broadly similar businesses and pay models;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies that compete for the same customers with similar products and/or services; and</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies with whom we may
compete for executive talent.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In connection with its annual review in 2020, the Committee removed two companies from the peer group (Ingersoll-Rand plc and Raytheon
Company) based on transactions that occurred during the year. The Committee then added two peers (Ecolab Inc. and Trane Technologies plc) that met the criteria summarized to the right. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The revenue median of the peer group was $18.0&nbsp;billion based on the twelve-month average of reported financial results through
June&nbsp;30, 2020, and the median market capitalization was $29.3&nbsp;billion, versus $13.8&nbsp;billion and $52.8&nbsp;billion, respectively, for ITW. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The nature
of our decentralized and diverse lines of business presents challenges in identifying similar organizations for comparison purposes; however, we believe that the peer group selected provides relevant comparisons. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Decisions and Individual Compensation Levels </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On an annual basis, the CEO reviews the total compensation of the NEOs and makes recommendations to the Committee based on his assessment of each executive&#146;s
individual performance and peer group compensation information. The Committee makes recommendations to the independent directors regarding the CEO&#146;s compensation based on an assessment of the CEO&#146;s performance and peer group compensation
information. There are no material differences in the policies and decision processes used in setting compensation for the CEO and the other NEOs. However, the different levels of compensation for the NEOs, as shown in the Summary Compensation Table
of this proxy statement, reflect internal factors such as each executive&#146;s scope of responsibility, performance, impact on profitable growth and breadth of experience, as well as compensation data from the peer group. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">33 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom53919_17"></A><A NAME="tx53919_54"></A>Components of the 2020 Executive
Compensation Program </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx53919_55"></A>Base Salary </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In
determining base salary, the CEO and the Committee consider the size and scope of the executive officers&#146; responsibilities, experience, performance, market data and the median base salary of similar positions at our peer group companies. The
Committee believes that median base salary is an appropriate general reference point to use for encouraging solid performance. Base salaries are reviewed annually, and adjustments are intended to recognize performance and contributions over the
prior year, as well as any significant changes in duties or scope of responsibility. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2020, the Committee recommended a base salary increase of 2.7&nbsp;percent
for Mr.&nbsp;Santi, which was approved by the Board&#146;s independent directors. For the other NEOs, the Committee approved recommended base pay merit increases ranging from 3.5 to 4.5&nbsp;percent. These base salary increases were effective
February&nbsp;24, 2020. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx53919_56"></A>Annual Executive Incentive Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that executives generally should be rewarded for their contributions to the overall financial success measured by income and organic growth of the Company as
a whole, and, if applicable, the business segment he or she leads. Achieving our annual financial objectives is important to executing on our current strategic objectives and delivering long-term value to stockholders. The Committee determines and
approves the performance results and awards for the NEOs and recommends for approval, and the independent directors of the full Board approve the annual incentive award amount for the CEO. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The annual Executive Incentive Plan (EIP) is composed solely of financial performance measures for our NEOs. For 2020, the financial metric weighting for Mr.&nbsp;Santi,
Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Herlihy and Mr.&nbsp;Larsen is based 60&nbsp;percent on Company operating income and 40&nbsp;percent on Company organic revenue growth. For Mr.&nbsp;Martindale and Mr.&nbsp;Hartnett, the weighting of the financial measures is based
60&nbsp;percent on operating income and 40&nbsp;percent on organic revenue growth, with 50&nbsp;percent of each metric based on Company results and 50&nbsp;percent on results of their respective business segments. The financial measures were
recommended by management and approved by the Committee at the start of the performance year. While the Committee has the discretion to make adjustments in the calculation of financial performance to eliminate factors beyond the control of
management and to eliminate possible disincentives to act in the long-term best interests of the Company and our stockholders, the Committee did not make any adjustments to the 2020 EIP plan or plan payouts due to the impact of the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">COVID-19</FONT> pandemic on financial results. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2020 EIP Financial Measures </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2020, executive officers were eligible to earn a payment according to the performance scales below. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2020 EIP Company Financial Targets </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">(as&nbsp;a&nbsp;%&nbsp;of<BR>Base&nbsp;Salary)</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx53919_57"></A>Long-Term Incentives </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="61%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="38%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The value of the overall long-term incentive award for the</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">CEO is determined by the Committee, subject to approval by the independent directors of the full Board of Directors. Awards to other NEOs are
recommended by&nbsp;the CEO to the Committee for approval.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-right:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The key
factors in determining the awards are the executive&#146;s position, performance, potential to contribute to the long-term success of the Company, breadth of experience and prior awards. In addition, although we generally do not establish any
specific target or prescribed value in relation to the peer group, comparisons are made to long-term incentive levels in the peer group and market compensation data.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Long-term Incentive Philosophy</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that ensuring the long-term growth and profitability of the business is a primary management responsibility. Therefore, a significant portion of an executive
officer&#146;s compensation should be directly linked to key financial performance measures that consider the long-term perspective, such as operating margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC, EPS and ITW&#146;s share price
over time.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">35 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2020, the NEOs received 50&nbsp;percent of the value of their awards in the form of stock options and
50&nbsp;percent of the value in other performance-based awards (25&nbsp;percent payable in PSUs and 25&nbsp;percent payable in cash). We believe that stock options are an effective incentive because they directly align the interest of the executives
with those of our stockholders, as an unexercised stock option has no realizable value if our stock price is below the exercise price, while the value increases along with increases in our stock price above the exercise price. The stock option
awards are combined with the other performance-based awards to closely align the realized value of long-term incentives with the financial performance objectives of the Company&#146;s strategy and total shareholder return. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2020 Long-Term Incentive Award Weightings</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="34%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="32%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="32%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Stock<BR>Options</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">PSUs</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Performance<BR>Cash</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>



<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">50%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">25%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">25%</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has established specific vesting and expiration provisions associated with termination of employment due to death,
disability and retirement, as defined in the applicable awards, and forfeiture provisions upon other termination of employment. The Committee, in its sole discretion, may deem a long-term incentive award, whether vested or unvested, to be
immediately forfeited if the recipient competes with the Company, engages in gross misconduct or conduct that is against the business interests of the Company, or divulges confidential information about the Company to others. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I></I></B><B>2020 Stock Option Awards</B><B><I> </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The 2020 stock options vest in equal installments over a four-year period ending in 2024. Stock options are awarded with an exercise price equal to the fair market value
of the common stock on the date of grant and normally expire ten years after the award date. The Committee awards only <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options because it believes that the tax benefits to the Company of <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options outweigh the potential tax benefits to the NEOs of incentive stock options. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I></I></B><B>2020-2022 Performance Share Units and Performance Cash Awards</B><B><I> </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The PSUs and Performance Cash awards vest three years from the date of grant, subject to the achievement of the performance goals set at the beginning of the performance
period. PSUs are awarded based on the fair market value of one share of ITW common stock on the date of award. Dividend equivalents are accrued and added as units to the original PSU awards as reinvested dividends. These reinvested dividends are
paid only on PSUs earned at the end of the performance period. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The goals for the 2020 PSUs and Performance Cash awards are equally weighted and based on three-year
average operating margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC and EPS growth. The payout range is 50&nbsp;percent to 200&nbsp;percent of the target award for threshold to maximum performance. Performance below threshold results in
no payout for the weighted portion for that metric. The payout at the end of the performance period will be based on the following payout scale: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="92%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">EPS Growth
(1/3rd)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">-14.3%</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">0.9%</TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><B>Total&nbsp;Payout:&nbsp;89.7%&nbsp; </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; text-indent:-1%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">* For purposes of determining 2018 EPS growth, 2017 EPS excludes the unfavorable impact of $1.90 for the discrete tax charge related to
the 2017 U.S. tax legislation and the favorable impact of $0.17 for the confidential legal settlement. <B></B> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I></I></B><B>Timing of
Long-Term Incentive Awards</B><B><I> </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee meets in February of each year following the Company&#146;s public release of its earnings results
for the recently completed fiscal year to consider and act with respect to long-term incentive awards for the executive officers. Long-term awards are made in compliance with the Long-Term Incentive Plan, including the requirement that stock options
may not be awarded at less than 100&nbsp;percent of the fair market value of ITW&#146;s common stock on the date of grant. The exercise price of the awards is based on the closing price of ITW&#146;s stock on the date of award. We do not time award
grant dates for the purpose of enhancing the value of executive compensation. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom53919_18"></A><A NAME="tx53919_58"></A>Compensation Governance Practices and Policies
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="rom_153919_68"></A>Stock Ownership Guidelines </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that stock ownership is important because it aligns the interests of our management and directors with those of our stockholders and mitigates
compensation-related risk. Because of the importance of stock ownership, the Board of Directors and the Committee have adopted stock ownership guidelines for executive officers and directors. The guidelines for stock ownership as a multiple of
executive officers&#146; base salaries and of directors&#146; annual cash retainers are as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:8pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Title</FONT></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

Officer</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee expects that an executive officer or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director will
achieve the applicable ownership level within five years. The achievement of these guidelines is reviewed annually. The Board of Directors believes that its stock ownership guidelines are appropriate, reasonable and attainable given the
responsibilities and compensation levels of our executive officers and directors and has not deemed it necessary to impose a holding period requirement for shares owned by our executive officers and directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All executive officers and directors who have been in their positions for five or more years have met or exceeded the applicable stock ownership guidelines. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Hedging and Anti-Pledging Policy </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Pursuant
to the Company&#146;s Hedging/Anti-Pledging Policy, all employees (including executive officers) and directors that receive equity-based awards from the Company are prohibited from trading ITW options or engaging in short sales of ITW stock. In
addition, all executive officers and directors and their designees are prohibited from purchasing or selling any financial instrument or otherwise engaging in any transaction that hedges or offsets, or is designed to hedge or offset, any decrease in
the market value of ITW equity securities. In addition, since April 2013, our executive officers and directors have been prohibited from pledging ITW stock, and all pledged shares are excluded from ownership for purposes of our stock ownership
guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Recovery Policy </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We maintain a Compensation Recovery Policy (clawback policy) applicable to all executive officers of the Company subject to Section&nbsp;16 of the Securities Exchange
Act of 1934. Under the policy, the Committee will seek reimbursement of incentives paid to executive officers in the prior three years where the payment was predicated upon the achievement of certain financial results with respect to the applicable
performance period that was subsequently the subject of a material restatement due to material <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-compliance</FONT> of the Company with any financial reporting requirement under the U.S. securities laws. The
reimbursement amount is equal to the excess of the gross incentive payment made over the gross payment that would have been made if the original payment had been determined based on the restated financial results. Further, following a material
restatement of our financial statements, we will seek reimbursement of compensation and profits from trading in Company stock received by our CEO and CFO to the extent required under Section&nbsp;304 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>2020 Risk Assessment </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee,
together with management and Cook, annually considers potential risks when reviewing our compensation programs for all employees, including our executive officers. Based on this assessment, the Committee concluded that our 2020 compensation programs
do not create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on ITW. In making this determination, the Committee reviewed the key design elements of our compensation programs, as well as the means by which any potential risks may
be mitigated, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">A Balanced Mix of Compensation Components &#151; The target compensation mix for our executive officers is composed of base
salary, annual cash incentives and long-term cash and equity incentives, representing a mix that is not overly weighted toward short-term cash incentives. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Multiple Performance Factors &#151; Our incentive compensation plans use Company-wide measures, which encourage focus on
the achievement of objectives for the overall benefit of the Company. Multiple financial goals also prevent an overemphasis on any one metric. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">38 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Long-Term Incentives &#151; Our long-term incentives are primarily equity-based, and our PSUs and Performance Cash awards
are subject to performance goals. These long-term incentives have three-year vesting schedules (PSUs and Performance Cash) or four-year vesting schedules (stock options), in each case to complement our annual cash-based incentives.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

200&nbsp;percent of target. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Stock Ownership Guidelines &#151; Our guidelines call for significant share ownership, which further aligns the interests
of our executive officers and directors with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Clawback Policy &#151; Our Compensation Recovery Policy authorizes the Committee to recoup past incentive compensation in
the event of a material restatement of the Company&#146;s financial results. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Prohibition on Hedging and Pledging &#151; Executive officers and directors are subject to Company policy that prohibits
hedging and pledging activities with respect to ITW stock. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
